description: 1997 a loser of a year so far?  MAD takes one last shot at turning it all around with parodies of "G.I. Jane," "Pop-Up Videos" and "Siskel & Ebert," and more fun with "Melvin & Jenkins" and Peter Kuper's stylish version of "Spy vs. Spy."

Dark Horse continues its presentation of the entirety of Japan's Lone Wolf and Cub, one of the unquestioned landmarks of graphic fiction, packaged in the digest format preferred by creator Goseki Kojima. The fourth volume of this ambitious monthly program collects four classic Lone Wolf tales, including one never before seen in America, where little Daigoro searches for his lost father while amazing a well-known samurai with his warrior's eyes and cool demeanor. Also, the Lone Wolf takes on the sons of the war-bell warden, legions of organized crime bosses, and a mysterious tattooed lady with a dark story and impeccable killing skills. It's bloody and romantic...and among the best the comics medium has to offer.

Story Titles

  • The Bell Warden
  • Unfaithful Retainers
  • Parting Frost
  • Performer
name: The Bell Warden

description:
This volume contains five powerful, classic tales of the assassin Itto Ogami, the Lone Wolf, as he continues his journey to hell. The Yagyu clan, fearful of the growing legend surrounding Lone Wolf, has decided to protect itself by sending its own assassin after him, and later pit the greatest swordsman of a rival clan against him. Also, Lone Wolf must face the leader of a bounty-hunting gang who seeks revenge against Ogami for slaying his young lord years ago, and a master gunsmith who values the art of warfare above all else and will change his life forever. Don't miss a single volume of the acclaimed epic series that belongs on every bookshelf: Lone Wolf and Cub.

Story Titles

  • Trail Markers
  • Executioner's Hill
  • Black Wind
  • Decapitator Asemon
  • The Guns of Sakai
name: Black Wind

description:
The legend of Lone Wolf and Cub continues to grow in this latest chapter of Koike and Kojima's epic samurai masterpiece chronicling the wanderings of Japan's deadliest assassin, Itto Ogami, and his infant son, Daigoro. In this volume, Ogami takes on the most dangerous killer of the countryside, foils the plans of a deceptive gambling troupe, tricks an evil lord into exposing his weak underbelly, and pits himself against the Shogun's dangerous and deadly Kurokawa ninja! Drawing extensively from Sun Tzu's The Art of War, and featuring the saddest puppy-dog story ever published, this must-have volume is packed with action and emotion.

Story Titles

  • Lanterns for the Dead
  • Deer Chaser
  • Hunger Town
  • The Soldier is the Castle
  • One Stone Bridge
name: Lanterns for the Dead

description:
There is more than just blood between parent and child. Itto Ogami and his son Daigoro have seen more blood flowing from more bodies than anyone in Edo, but what connects them is their spirit and path. In this collection of classic stories, Itto must protect a young girl after her family is destroyed by a cunning courtesan. Meanwhile, Itto's arch-enemy, Yagyu Retsudo, has sent the civilian police force to round up the Lone Wolf as a common criminal, and before long, Daigoro is coincidentally tangled in a messy pair of crimes. And, most dramatically, Itto returns to the scene of one of his past executions to enter a tender and honorable sword fight against an executed lord's former retainer.

Story Titles

  • Dragnet
  • Night Stalker
  • Cloud Dragon, Wind Tiger
  • Inn of the Last Chrysanthemum
  • Penal Code Article Seventy-Nine
name: Cloud, Dragon, Wind Tiger

description:
The journey of vengeance in blood and honor continues. Under the itinerant thumb of Yagyu Retsudo, the Shogun's secret ninja warriors, the Kurokuwa clan, attempt to ensnare Ogami. Can the Lone Wolf break the chains? If so, there are many in line behind Yagyu waiting to challenge the masterful swordsman, such as a vengeful widow, numerous police, and the freezing cold of winter itself. Plus, read the story of Ogami's rise to the position of the Shogun's Officer of Death, feel the seething root of Retsudo Yagyu's bitterness against Ogami, and watch Ogami teach a proud thief about true honor and the wages of deception. Five action-packed chapters, including never-before-translated material, are included in the latest volume of this classic series. Read it on the bullet train to Edo!

Story Titles

  • Tidings of the Geese
  • The Frozen Crane
  • Chains of Death
  • The Infinite Path
  • Thread of Tears
  • Beku-no-ji
name: Chains of Death

description:
Water, death, and angry ninja take the foreground in this exciting volume of the legendary Lone Wolf and Cub series! A pitiful ferryboat girl discovers the tragic ways of "A Wife of the Heart," as the Lone Wolf, Ogami Itto, stands against the man she loves. In "Wayward Swords," a rogue swordsman-for-hire learns a valuable lesson about Bushido, the Way of the Warrior, from the Lone Wolf. Afterwards, Ogami once again must face the treachery of the Kurokuwa ninja clan, then becomes a river porter to foil the secret plans of his enemy, the Yagyu clan, and in doing so declares war against them all! The Lone Wolf's actions lead to a nationwide manhunt and an epic, bloody battle unlike any in comics. Don't dare miss a volume of the series that belongs on every bookshelf: Lone Wolf and Cub.

Story Titles

  • Wife of the Heart
  • Wandering Samurai
  • Echo of the Assassin
  • Naked Worms
  • The Yagyu Letter: Prologue
name: Echo of the Assassin

description:
The six paths and four lives are split asunder, as Itto Ogami and Daigoro become separated in one of this series' most powerful stories to date! The Lone Wolf's arch-enemy, Yagyu Retsudo, pursues Ogami to retrieve the secret letter stolen from him, only to watch dozens of his men fall victim to the Lone Wolf's hungry sword! But Yagyu drives father and son apart as they tumble down a cliff and must survive on their own! Little Daigoro must begin his honorable search for his father. But with Yagyu's henchmen hunting high and low for the Lone Wolf and his cub, the net drags closer and the danger wraps tighter, but the blood flows ever freely...

Story Titles

  • The Yagyu Letter
  • The Tears of Daigoro
  • The Fisherwoman's Love
  • Drifting Shadows
  • Straw Boy
name: Hostage Child

description: This is it...the final showdown between Nate Grey and Psi-Ops! But where do Ness' loyalties lie, and what secret does he know that could change the outcome of the battle?
name: Uninvited Guests

description: How can even the powerful X-Man hope to defeat the Psi-Ops when they have the entire world on their side? Get ready for the most shocking showdown as Nate engages his most tenacious adversaries in a battle not everyone will walk away from. Plus, a last page shocker not to be missed.
name: All Fall Down

description: A piece of Nate's Age of Apocalypse reality has merged with an Alaskan mountain and he has to fight through an army of Infintes with Cyclops and Jean by his side to try and set things right.
name: In Cold Blood

description: Nate Grey encounters a cult of mutant transcendent telepaths known as The Gauntlet set in their ways exploring their existence rather than imply mutant politics. A hostile being from a ravaged Earth sets to kill these mutant explorers less Nate intervenes.
name: No Direction Home: part two: Nowhere to hide

description: Nate Grey explores his last battle with the Broken Man as to gain further insight of his agenda against the Gauntlet for their multidimensional travels and piracy. A tragic truth is revealed as Nate suspects he's fighting the wrong monster.
name: No Direction Home: part three: Lost Worlds

description: Nate returns to The Gauntlet's reality as to vindicate the Broken Man of his loss and punish the Gauntlet of their secreted evils. Reflecting to his own role as a shaman healer to his executions, X-Man upheavals a hollow victory.
name: No Direction Home: Part Four: Counter X

description: Exploring the realms of Cuba with the being of Madelyne Pryor, Nate Grey learns that he has committed a psychic assault by her actions onto innocents. Madelyne sets her own worldly goals with Nate as she sends him to her world.
name: Shockwave: part one: Infinities of Evil

description: Nate Grey learns that Madelyn Pryor is a parallel world's Red Queen turned absolute monarch. In a realm plagued with Civil Wars and expansion to her despot desires, she sets to use Nate Grey as a psychic weapon against the East to gain autonomy of her world and every world outside her dimension as well.
name: Shockwave: part two: Danger Signs

description: The most epic X-Man tale to date continues as Nate Grey suddenly finds himself face-to-face with...himself?! Startling secrets will be revealed and lives will be lost in the penultimate chapter to Shockwave.
name: Shockwave: part three: Double Vision

description: Get ready for the stunning conclusion to the most epic X-Man adventure yet. It's the tale that will change Nate Grey's life and the course of his future forever.
name: Shockwave: part four: Worlds Without End

description: A powerful new force threatens Nate's world and even the X-Man may not be able to stop it.
name: Fearful Symmetries Part 1

description: Nate Grey has discovered that Qabiri has been "cleansing" the lower realities - and now he's teaming with a group of super-humans to make sure the mad mutant doesn't reach our world! Even the X-Man may not be powerful enough to save a doomed world.
name: Fearful Symmetries part 2

description: Qabiri has come for Nate Grey and nothing can stand in his way. Has the X-Man finally met his match. Is this the one adversary that even he can not defeat. If Nate should fall then the world is doomed.
name: Fearful Symmetries part 3

description: The Exiles lose another member as they rush to save another earth from the planet-devouring Galactus. Who will be left behind? Who will take their place?
name: A World Apart (Part 3 of 3)

description:
The Team Titans are a group of teenaged heroes from the future sent back in time to kill Donna Troy. But why would they want to murder one of the greatest champions in the DCU?

Total Chaos part 3 of 9. Note: Five variant issues of #1 were released, each with a 19-page origin story dedicated to the featured member on the cover (Killowat, Mirage, Nightrider, Redwing, and Terra). The main story, part 3 of the Total Chaos crossover, is the same for each issue.

The Electrifying Secret Origin of Killowat

After saving Lord Chaos’ life from two rebellious Team Titans Anvil and Aurora, Charlie Watkins was promoted quite quickly in Lord Chaos’ security forces. Over time, Charlie became sympathetic to the Titans’ cause, becoming a double-agent. During a Team Titans’ mission, Charlie’s treachery was discovered by his best friend, also a guard. Charlie is killed, but comes back as an energy being and a full member of the Titans.

The Shape-Shifting Secret Origin of Mirage

The shape-shifter Mirage was trying to live her own life when she, her lover, and her child were the subject of a Lord Chaos raid. Mirage was captured, where her shape-shifting abilities were put to use as a brainwashed member of Lord Chaos’ guard. She becomes friends with another recruit, Abraham, whom she is forced to kill in gladiatorial combat. Mirage flees, saving the life of another meta-gene named Redbird. The two become part of the resistance.

Nightrider

Lord Chaos’ forces have invaded Transylvania, and have captured a fourteen-year-old boy named Dagon. The commander of Lord Chaos’ forces, Commander Stalg, is disgusted by the natives’ belief in the superstitious vampires. To prove them a lesson, he tries to create his own vampire using the bones of Dracula. He transforms Dagon into a vampire, and, when he decides to slaughter the people, they are transformed into a huge creature intent on revenge. Dagon becomes Nightrider, and frees his people.

The High-Flying Origin of Redwing

Years ago, two scientists, Paul and Karen Levine fell in love and became married. They gave birth to a young daughter, Carrie, who sprouted crimson wings, and a son Jon, who had the ability to speak to machines. They raised their daughter away from society, but when Lord Chaos took power, he ordered all meta-gene people to surrender themselves to the state. The Levines refused, and Lord Chaos’ troops killed them. Jon was captured, and Redwing rescued him, with the help of the rebel Mirage.

Terra

Terra has been recruited into the Team Titans. When the Titans ask her of her origin, she reveals that she is the daughter of the long-dead Geo-Force, the original Terra’s brother. The Titans’ mysterious “Leader” becomes suspicious, and with good reason: this Terra was created by Lord Chaos to discover the rebels’ hideout. This Terra, however, had no idea she was a mole, and turned on Lord Chaos to side with the Titans. Proving herself loyal, Terra becomes a full member of the Team Titans.

Childhood’s End

The mad titan from the future Lord Chaos has come to S.T.A.R. Labs to ensure his own birth. Lord Chaos, Deathstroke, the New Titans, and the Team Titans all fight each other, while Terry Long tries to get the pregnant Donna Troy to safety. Nightwing and Mirage call for a stop to the fighting, allowing Lord Chaos to escape with Donna Troy. The heroes regroup at one of Steve Dayton’s apartments, where the Team Titans tell the others about Lord Chaos’ horrible future, the future they call their home. The Titans speak of a world where Lord Chaos conquers the world, but where one hero, a member of the original Teen Titans rises up to create a resistance against Lord Chaos. This group, called the Team Titans, would stop at nothing to destroy Lord Chaos’ rule.

While the heroes learn about the future of Lord Chaos, Lord Chaos is ensuring his existence. Lord Chaos takes Donna Troy to a hidden location to protect her while giving birth. Donna gives birth to the baby Lord Chaos, which means Lord Chaos has no more need for Donna. Lord Chaos blasts Donna as he holds his past self in his hands.
name: Childhood's End

description:
Donna Troy is back, and she's not happy. Engorged with divine might, Troia has grown to be a 50-foot goddess bent on finding her son-- and not even her friends will stand in her way.

Total Chaos part 6 of 9. Donna Troy has been reincarnated after her death at the hands of Lord Chaos; except, this incarnation, Troia, is a 50-feet-tall mad god. She takes off to track down Lord Chaos on the moon, intent on rescuing her child. Starfire tries to stop her, but is unsuccessful. While the New Titans try to figure out what their next move is, the Team Titans have regrouped after their fight with the New Titans, but minus Mirage. The Team Titans decide they need to go back to the New Titans and team together against Lord Chaos.

The Team Titans go back to the New Titans, but the New Titans are prepared for another fight. Before they can come to blows, however, Lord Chaos appears. Now that he has killed his mother Donna Troy (or so he thinks), he has come to kill his father, Terry Long. While the combined might of the New Titans and Team Titans prepare to stand against Lord Chaos, another Team Titan from the future, named Battalion, has come back to the 20th century.
name: From the Ashes of Defeat

description:
It's the startling conclusion to the Team Titans and New Titans war with Lord Chaos!

Total Chaos part 9 of 9. Donna Troy, now the godlike and half-insane Troia, have brought the New Titans and Team Titans to the former site of Titans Tower. They, aided by Aqualad, plan on defeating Lord Chaos and rescue the newborn Robert Long. Lord Chaos, though, has opened a portal to his future, and has brought through his army. The heroes attack, and are confronted by the armies of Lord Chaos. As they fight, the Team Titans are joined by their old drill sergeant, Battalion, who has come back in time as well.

During the fight, the entire structure is teleported to the Planet of the Gods. Once there, Troia and Lord Chaos are confronted by the Titans of Myth. The Titans know that Lord Chaos is not of this world, and they erase him. They also realize that Donna Troy is not ready for the powers within her, and decide to remove them. The Titans remove the powers within both Donna Troy and her newborn son, allowing them to live normal lives. Donna and her husband Terry Long are reunited, and the heroes are returned to Earth.
name: Out of Chaos!

description:
The ill-tempered, gun-toting Battalion comes face-to-face with the macabre power of Judge and Jury.

Future Titans have gone mad are hunting down their former allies.
name: Judge and Jury

description: On one side are the macabre metahuman hunters known as Judge and Jury, on the other is the robotic fighting force known as Metallik, and stuck in the middle are the Team Titans.
name: Heavy Metallik

description: If the Team Titans are from ten years in the future, where are their present-day selves?
name: It Should Have Been A Wonderful Life

description: The Nightwing from the Team Titans' future arrives in the present, but is he here as friend or foe?
name: The Darkening Night, Part One: Heroes Aren't Born, They're Unmade!

description: Future Nightwing becomes the sinister Deathwing. Who is responsible for this startling transformation in the Team Titans' most trusted ally?
name: The Darkening Night, Part Two: Scarlet and Crystal

description: Mirage is in love with the Nightwing from the future, but, this Nightwing has been corrupted and is now the sinister villain known as Deathwing.
name: The Darkening Night, Part Three: Blood Light

description: Kilowatt faces Lazarium in a final battle from which only one of them will walking away.
name: You Can't Go Home Again Part 4

description: With Wonder Woman's help, Donna Troy petitions the Titans of Myth for her powers to return. What happens next may change her outlook on the future.
name: Facing the Future

description:
The team is thrown into turmoil when they are suddenly attacked by a menagerie of man-beasts. Worse yet, their encounter with the beasts is having an odd effect on Redwing.

The radioactive mess that was Quarac leads to sentient man-beasts that need guidance and help. Unfortunately the creatures don't know this.
name: Monsters in the Storm

description:
A bizarre change has come over Redwing. If the Team Titans can't figure out what it is or why, they may be murdered by their own teammate.

A radioactive wasteland is further complicated by delicate diplomatic issues and one of the Titans going insane.
name: Secrets in the Sand

description: A Zero Hour crossover issue. At time destabilizes, the members of the Team Titans and reserve members of the Teen Titans split up to provide damage control. Hero X, Metallik, Automaton, Backbeat, Bumblebee, and Mal Duncan protect Seattle. Prestor Jon brings Lapidus, Redwing, Mirage, and Killowat to protect the United Nations. Dagon, Hellebore, Murder Master and Battalion join Flamebird and the Protector to help the time-displaced Sanangelopolis, while Terra, Wonder Boy, Green, Human Mystery, and Aqualad protect the Sanangelopolis coastline. As the heroes protect civilians from time-displaced hazards, the mysterious creator of the Team Titans, Hank Hall, prepares to make his final move.
name: All Good Things...

description: An abused, alienated teenaged girl becomes the latest victim of an alien parasite attack, surviving to become Chimera, a hero with the ability to create bizarre and nightmarish images with her mind.
name: In The Mind Of Chimera

description:
The Elseworlds Annuals, the DC Universe's journey into remote realms of possibility, continue as the Team Titans are in the farthest reaches of space, in an evil galactic empire ruled by Lord Chaos. But Chaos's rule is challenged by a rebel alliance in search of a leader...a leader that emerges from among the core membership of the Team Titans.

The Titans re-imagined work as a peacekeeping force in the far future.
name: Into the Light

description: It seems as if Xanthi's death is the end of the Titans. But Nightwing proposes that can be the third Seed. Gar Logan and Raven attack and Raven swallows , meeting the two seeds inside. In New Titans #55, the Titans return to Earth. New Cronus and the Spartans are now allied, and on the way home, Athyns is dropped of Xanthi's world to give him a proper burial. When Donna reaches Earth, she meets her very missed husband. Donna Troy then reveals her gifts which New Cronus gave. The gift is a new costume made by a Titan couple and a new haircut to go with it. In this issue, she also reveals her new name: Troia
name: Who is Wonder Girl? Chapter 5: Answers and Questions!

description: "Transition!" Guest-starring Batman. In the stunning aftermath to last issue's epic events, the Titans return home to find that things have changed. Nightwing learns that his predecessor to the Robin mantle, Jason Todd, has been murdered, and confronts his former mentor about it. One member is asked to leave the team. And Wonder Girl is no more. From now on Donna Troy will be known as Troia!
name: Transition

description: Double-sized Tenth Anniversary issue - "Beginnings...Endings...and (We Promise), New Beginnings!" Part 1 of 9. Deathstroke cameo. The Titans plan to celebrate their Tenth Anniversary, but ruthlessly and systematically Wildebeest takes down each of them. Only one man may be able to save them. The only other person to so soundly defeat the heroes himself - Deathstroke the Terminator!
name: Beginnings... Endings... And (We Promise) New Beginnings!

description: "Death of a Hero!" Part 2 of 9. Guest-starring Deathstroke, Golden Eagle, and Aqualad. The hunt for the Titans turns deadly, as one hero falls. Can Deathstroke piece together the clues that will help him find his son and Jericho's missing teammates before it's too late?
name: Death of a Hero!

description: "The Once and Future...!" Meet the all New Teen Titans - Nightrider, Kilowatt, Mirage, Redwing, and...Terra?! Yeah, that's right, Terra! Where did this new group of teenage heroes come from, and what is their mission?
name: Once and Future...
War of the Gods, Part 23: ... And They Call the Wind Pariah!
